                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1456-1">Biographie : Bedjan, Jab-Alaha, 288-331 ; BHO, 1032.
Autres references : Fiey, Assyrie chretienne, III, 56-60.
M. Tamcke, Der Katholikos-Patriarch Sabrisho' I und das Monchtums (Frankfurt et
Bern, 1988).
BSO, II, 916- 17 (J .M. Fiey).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1456">In hagiography: Sawrisho was a student of
            the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/476">School of Nisibis</placeName>. He
          became a monk of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/637">Mount Qardu</placeName> and
          performed many miracles. He became a bishop and played a role in the conversion
            of <persName>Al Numan, the Lakhmid phylarch</persName>. Under the influence
            of <persName>Khusro II</persName>, he became the Catholicos of the Church of the
          East.</note>
                    <note type="misc" source="#bib1456-1">What kind of date is this?</note>
